      <memberdef kind="function" id="hotcross_8h_1abab2cd64f544ce16dca27fabd79c67aa" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>__host__ void</type>
        <definition>__host__ void init_hotcross</definition>
        <argsstring>(void)</argsstring>
        <name>init_hotcross</name>
        <param>
          <type>void</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Initializes the Compton cross-section lookup table. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function prepares a 2D lookup table for the total Compton cross-section as a function of dimensionless photon frequency <formula id="2">$ w $</formula> and electron temperature <formula id="3">$ \Theta_e $</formula>.</para>
<para><bold>Routine</bold>:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Attempts to open the file specified by <computeroutput>HOTCROSS</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>If the file is found, it loads the precomputed values into memory.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>If the file is missing, it triggers a numerical calculation of the table using <computeroutput><ref refid="hotcross_8h_1ab54b19afffd3bd0cb19e5a53d90376ac" kindref="member">total_compton_cross_num()</ref></computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>The table is stored in <formula id="4">$ \log_{10}-\log_{10} $</formula> space.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>void </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="src/hotcross.h" line="26" column="15" declfile="src/hotcross.h" declline="26" declcolumn="15"/>
