      <memberdef kind="function" id="hotcross_8h_1a859f826ad10e384da3310b701a67ae3f" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>__device__ double</type>
        <definition>__device__ double total_compton_cross_lkup</definition>
        <argsstring>(double w, double thetae, const double *d_table_ptr)</argsstring>
        <name>total_compton_cross_lkup</name>
        <param>
          <type>double</type>
          <declname>w</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>double</type>
          <declname>thetae</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const double *</type>
          <declname>d_table_ptr</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Computes the total Compton cross-section via lookup table and approximations. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function selects the optimal physical regime to calculate the cross-section based on photon frequency <formula id="2">$ w $</formula> and electron temperature <formula id="3">$ \Theta_e $</formula>.</para>
<para><bold>Routine</bold>:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para><bold>Thomson</bold>: If <formula id="5">$ w \Theta_e &lt; 10^{-6} $</formula>, returns the Thomson cross-section.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Klein-Nishina</bold>: If below table temperature limits, uses analytical expressions.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Interpolation</bold>: If in-bounds, performs bilinear interpolation in <formula id="4">$ \log_{10}-\log_{10} $</formula> space.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Fallback</bold>: If out-of-bounds, triggers a direct numerical calculation.</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>w</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Dimensionless photon frequency. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>thetae</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Dimensionless electron temperature. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>d_table_ptr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Restrict-qualified pointer to the device lookup table.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>The calculated Compton cross-section. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
